    "reconcile_line": "Drafter-gap-reduction feasibility (#481 Dir-4 analytic leg). #489 fixed the breach at 24.31% for ANY spec-alive config (Delta=4.295%); closing it needs the 3.661% ACCEPTANCE bucket itself. INVERTING #489: breach<5% <=> Delta<=3.334% <=> reduce acceptance 0.960pp (26.2% of bucket); breach<1% <=> Delta<=2.644% <=> reduce 1.651pp (45.1%). MECHANISM: the gap is a RATIO -- raising INTRINSIC a_1 (EAGLE-3 arch fusion, the cliff 0.729->~0.77-0.91) does NOT close it: under BOTH shift models it mildly WORSENS (mult +0.383pp / add +0.169pp; longer chains compound a fixed per-position shift) -> a_1 is the SPEED axis, NOT a gap-closer. Only SHIFT-REDUCTION closes it. LITERATURE (SambaNova 2503.07807, mild-shift): arch-alone 10-25% (0.37-0.92pp -> MISSES breach<5%), wider data-mix 25-50%, DOMAIN-TARGETED 60-80% (2.20-2.93pp -> CLEARS both bars). VERDICT fast_private_safe_strict_path_exists=True: a fast spec-alive config CAN be made private-safe, but ONLY by a wider-distribution-training drafter retrain, NOT by EAGLE-3 architecture alone and NOT by any public-TPS speed. HONESTY: analytic over literature priors (no published EAGLE-3 OOD a_1 exists); GO only justifies GPU spend to TRAIN + measure E_accept on a held-out shifted split. Floor-lock 161.70 stays the only MEASURED strict private-safe ship."
